<p>Adverb: Adverbs give information about adjectives, verbs, or other adverbs. For example, in the sentence "The bird is very fast" the adverb "very" gives information about the adjective "fast". In the sentence "I am very very sleepy" the adverb very is giving information about the adverb very. In the sentence "She quickly answered the questions" the adverb quickly describes how fast the person answered the questions.</p>
